    <SYNOPSIS>
     Model of continuum emission due to recombination
    </SYNOPSIS>

   
 <DESC>
  <PARA>
         A model of the continuum emission due to recombination,
         taking the functional form:
  </PARA>

  <PARA>
    If x &gt;= refer,
  </PARA>

  <PARA>
   <EQUATION>
           f(x) = ampl*exp(-(x - refer)**2/(refer*fwhm/c/2.354820044)**2/2)
      </EQUATION>
  </PARA>

  <PARA>
    and if x &lt; refer,
  </PARA>

  <PARA>
   <EQUATION>  
           f(x) = ampl*(refer/x)**2 * exp-(1.440E8*(1/x - 1/refer)/temperature)
      </EQUATION>
  </PARA>

 
